OPERATING STATEMENT
1. INTRODUCTORY STATEMENT
1.1 This Operating Statement describes how Kinder Morgan Keystone Gas Storage LLC ("Keystone" or "KGS"), shall provide Firm and Interruptible Storage and related transportation Services, as well as Parking, Loaning, and Wheeling services, pursuant to Section 284.224 of the regulations of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, 18 C. F. R. ? 284.224. KGS reserves the right not to offer or commence any Service, or to discontinue any Interruptible Service if, in KGS's sole discretion, any impairment of intrastate Firm Service could result.
1.2 From time to time it may become necessary to update or revise this Operating Statement. At such time, KGS will serve on all Customers a copy of the proposed updates or revisions. KGS shall have the right to propose, file and make effective with the FERC, revisions to this Operating Statement for the purpose of changing the provisions thereof effective as to the Customer, except that KGS shall have no right to alter the rates or fees for Services rendered pursuant to a fully executed Services Agreement, except such alterations to the rates or fees that are specifically permitted pursuant to a specific Services Agreement. The filing of such applicable changes and revisions to this Operating Statement shall be without prejudice to the right of the Customer to contest or oppose the effectiveness of such filing.
2. DEFINITIONS
In this Agreement, any Services Agreement and in any Confirmations or Nominations made pursuant to a Services Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings given below. Where appropriate, the plural shall be deemed to include the singular and the singular shall contain the plural.
2.1 "Agreement" means the terms of this Operating Statement together with the applicable Services Agreement (including all Schedules) as such may be amended and supplemented from time to time.
2.2 "Btu" means one British thermal unit and is defined as the amount of heat required to raise the temperature of one (1) pound of water from fifty-nine degrees Fahrenheit (59? F) to sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60? F) at a constant pressure of fourteen and seventy-three hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.73 psia). Total Btus shall be determined by multiplying the total volume of natural gas delivered times the gas heating value expressed in Btus per cubic foot of natural gas adjusted on a dry basis.
2.3 "Business Day" means Monday through Friday, excluding Federal Banking Holidays.
2.4 "Commodity Charge" means the commodity fee for all Services, as agreed to by KGS and Customer and stated in the applicable Confirmation, multiplied by the number of Btus of Gas, including Fuel, Delivered by Customer to KGS at the Receipt Point or Delivered by KGS to Customer at the Delivery Point.
2.4(a) "Completion Rate" means the fee per MMBtu payable by Customer for Gas paid back to Transporter for completion of a Loan or on Gas withdrawn for a completion of a Park as stated in an applicable Confirmation.
2.5 "Confirmation" means a form setting forth the terms of a Transaction that is effective in accordance with this Operating Statement and the applicable Services Agreement, substantially in the form attached as Schedules "A", "B", "C" and "D" for the Service(s) to be provided for a Transaction.
2.6 "Central Time" means Central Standard Time or Central Daylight Time, as applicable.
2.7 "Customer" means anyone who has executed a Services Agreement with KGS.
2.8 "Customer Inventory" means the sum of the quantities of Gas Delivered by Customer to KGS at the Receipt Point(s) and stored, transported or parked in the Facilities for Customer's account, less the sum of the quantities of Gas Delivered by KGS to Customer at the Delivery Point(s), and less any Fuel. There will be a separate Customer Inventory maintained for each Confirmation.
2.9 "Daily Reference Price" means the lowest price of the range of prices reported as the daily "Absolute" price for "El Paso-Permian" on the Natural Gas Intelligence ("NGI") Daily Gas Price Index. If this publication is not available, KGS will use, as a substitute, a daily, published price representative of Gas in the Permian Basin Area.
2.10 "Day" or "Daily" means a period of 24 consecutive Hours beginning and ending at 9 o'clock a.m. Central Time, or such other time period as NAESB may define as a "day" for the purposes of Nominations, measurement or for other operational reasons.
2.11 "Deliver," "Delivery" or "Delivered" means the physical transfer of custody of Gas (or of natural gas in limited circumstances as set forth in Section 15.3) to or from the Facilities and, when applicable to a Loaning Service, may include Redelivered Gas.
2.12 "Delivery Point(s)" means the point at which KGS Delivers Gas to Customer or for Customer's account. Unless otherwise stated in the applicable Confirmation, the Delivery Point will be the Storage Withdrawal Point.
2.13 "Demand Charge" means the Monthly fee paid for Firm Storage, Parking and Loaning Services made available to Customer regardless of any quantities injected or withdrawn or associated with Initial or Completion Rates for a Transaction, as agreed to by KGS and Customer in the applicable Confirmation, including a fee per MMBtu multiplied by the number of MMBtus of Firm Storage Services available to Customer.
2.14 "Excess Inventory Rate" means either the Daily or Monthly fee per MMBtu payable by Customer, as appropriate, for Customer Inventory that (1) remains in the Facilities beyond the termination date of a Confirmation, or (2) exceeds at any time during the term of a Confirmation the Customer's Reserved Storage Capacity, Maximum Interruptible Inventory or Maximum Aggregate Parking Quantity pursuant to such Confirmation.
2.15 "Extended Loaning Rate" means either the Daily or Monthly fee per MMBtu payable by Customer for Gas that Customer has failed to Redeliver to KGS for a Transaction for Loaning Services at the termination of the applicable Transaction Period, as stated in the applicable Loaning Service Confirmation.
2.16 "Facilities" means the underground natural gas storage caverns, the storage wells, surface facilities, pipelines (which, for clarity, includes the Pipeline Facilities) and appurtenances thereto owned and operated by KGS in Winkler County, Texas.
2.17 "Federal Banking Holiday" means a holiday observed by the Federal Reserve Bank in Dallas, Texas.
2.18 "FERC" means the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
2.19 "Firm" means a Service that is not subject to a prior claim by another Customer of KGS or another type of Service and receives the same priority as any other type of Firm Service as further described in Section 17 of this Operating Statement, subject to the Force Majeure provisions and other terms and conditions of the Agreement.
2.20 "Force Majeure" has the meaning provided in Section 11 of this Operating Statement.
2.21 "Fuel" means the quantity of Gas, expressed as a percentage of the MMBtus of Gas injected into the Facilities for any Transaction, that Customer provides to KGS as fuel in connection with the Services provided, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.22 "Gas" means natural gas meeting the most restrictive of the quality standards and specifications of this Operating Statement and of the Interconnecting Pipelines connected to the Facilities.
2.23 "Hour" means a period of sixty (60) minutes.
2.24 "Imbalance" means the difference between the Gas volumes actually delivered and/or received by Customer and the Gas volumes nominated and confirmed for receipt and/or delivery at the Facilities.
2.25 "Initial Rate" means the fee per MMBtu payable by Customer for Gas tendered for Park or taken for Loan as stated in an applicable Confirmation.
2.25(a) "Interconnecting Pipeline" means the transporting pipeline directly connected to one or more Storage Withdrawal Point(s) or Storage Receipt Point(s).
2.26 "Interruptible" means a Service that is interruptible at any time for any reason, as further set out in Section 7.1 of this Operating Statement.
2.27 "Inventory/Balance Rate" means the fee per MMBtu payable by Customer for the volume of Customer Inventory or Loaned Quantities under a Transaction as stated in an applicable Confirmation.
2.28 "Loaned Quantities" means the sum of the quantities of Gas Delivered by KGS to Customer for Customer's account less the quantities of Gas Redelivered to KGS by Customer at the Receipt Point, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.29 "Loaning Service" is a Service that allows Customer to receive Gas from KGS for Customer's short-term use and then return a thermally equivalent quantity of Gas at a specified time. Customer will receive a stated quantity of Gas at the Delivery Point and after the specified time Customer will Redeliver a thermally equivalent quantity of Gas to the Receipt Point, in accordance with the terms of the applicable Confirmations. Loaning Service may be Firm or Interruptible.
2.30 "Market Price" means the highest price of the range of prices reported as the daily "Absolute" price for "El Paso-Permian" on the Natural Gas Intelligence ("NGI") Daily Gas Price Index. If this publication is not available, KGS will use, as a substitute, a daily, published price representative of Gas in the Permian Basin Area.
2.31 "Maximum Aggregate Loaning Quantity" means the maximum aggregate quantity of Gas that Customer is entitled to receive from KGS under a Transaction for Loaning Service, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.32 "Maximum Aggregate Parking Quantity" means the maximum aggregate quantity of Gas that Customer may maintain in the Facilities at any time under a Transaction for Parking Services, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.33 "Maximum Daily Injection Quantity" or "MDIQ" means the maximum quantity of Gas that Customer may inject into the Facilities on any Day as part of a Transaction for Storage Service, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.34 "Maximum Daily Loan Quantity" means the maximum quantity of Gas that Customer is entitled to receive from KGS on any Day for a Transaction for Loaning Services, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.35 "Maximum Daily Return Quantity" means the maximum quantity of Gas that Customer is entitled to Redeliver to KGS on any Day for a Transaction for Loaning Services, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.36 "Maximum Daily Transportation Quantity" or "MDTQ" means the maximum quantity of Gas that Customer may transport through the Facilities on any Day for a Transaction for Wheeling Services, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.37 "Maximum Daily Withdrawal Quantity" or "MDWQ" means the maximum quantity of Gas that Customer may withdraw from the Facilities on any Day for a Transaction for Storage Services, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.38 "Maximum Interruptible Storage Inventory" means the maximum Customer Inventory that can be stored as stated in a Schedule A for Interruptible Services.
2.39 "Mcf" means the quantity of Gas occupying one thousand (1,000) cubic feet at a temperature of sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60?F) and at a pressure of fourteen and seventy-three hundredths pounds per square inch absolute (14.73 psia).
2.40 "MMBtu" means a quantity of Gas containing one million (1,000,000) Btus.
2.41 "Month" or "Monthly" means a period of time beginning on the first Day of the calendar month and ending immediately prior to the commencement of the first Day of the next calendar month.
2.42 "NAESB" means the North American Energy Standards Board.
2.43 "Nomination" means a request by Customer to KGS for Services constituting a Transaction under an executed Confirmation.
2.44 Reserved.
2.45 "Overrun Rate" means the fee per MMBtu stated in the applicable Confirmation for Storage Services that will apply to any Nomination accepted by KGS that exceeds the Daily maximum quantity of Service available to Customer for that Transaction. The Overrun Rate will be stated as a maximum amount that can be charged.
2.46 "Parking Service" is a Service that provides for the short-term custody of a Customer's Gas at the Facilities. It involves the Delivery of a specified quantity of Gas by Customer to KGS at the Receipt Point and the subsequent Delivery of an equivalent quantity of Gas by KGS to Customer at the Delivery Point, in accordance with the terms of the applicable Confirmation(s). Parking Service may be Firm or Interruptible.
2.47 "Party" means either KGS or Customer.
2.48 "Pipeline Facilities" mean the pipelines owned by Keystone connecting its storage Facilities to the Interconnecting Pipelines and/or other Receipt Points or Delivery Points.
2.49 "Receipt Point" means the point at which KGS receives Gas for Customer's account. Unless otherwise stated in the applicable Confirmation, the Receipt Point will be the Storage Injection Point.
2.50 "Redeliver," "Redelivery" or "Redelivered" means Gas that is returned to KGS by Customer as part of a Loaning Services Transaction.
2.51 "Requesting Customer" means anyone who has requested Services or a Services Agreement from KGS, but has not executed a Services Agreement.
2.52 "Reserved Storage Capacity" means the maximum quantity of Gas that Customer may maintain in the Facilities at any time under a Transaction for Firm Storage or Parking Services, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.53 "Service" or "Services" means the types of storage and transportation services described in Section 1.1 of this Agreement.
2.54 "Services Agreement" means an Interstate Storage Services Agreement between KGS and a Customer.
2.55 "Storage Injection Point" and "Storage Withdrawal Point" means the point of interconnection of the Facilities and the meter station of the Interconnecting Pipeline(s), or another Receipt Point or Delivery Point, as designated in the Nomination.
2.56 "Storage Service" means a Service that allows Customer to inject, withdraw and/or store Gas at the Facilities during a stated period of time, subject to the rights, obligations and limitations stated in the applicable Services Agreement, and the applicable Confirmation.
2.57 "Transaction" means a Service provided to Customer under the terms of a Confirmation.
2.58 "Transaction Period" means the period of time during which a Transaction will be performed, as stated in the applicable Confirmation.
2.59 "Week" means a period of seven (7) consecutive Days beginning at 9:00 a.m. Central Time on each Monday and ending at the same on the next succeeding Monday.
2.60 "Wheeling Service" means an Interruptible Service that allows Customer to transport Gas through KGS's Pipeline Facilities between agreed-upon Receipt Point(s) and Delivery Point(s), subject to the obligations and limitations stated in the applicable Services Agreement and the applicable Confirmation(s).
3. INTERSTATE STORAGE SERVICES
3.1. Requests for Storage Services 3.1.1 From time to time, subject to KGS having available capacity, Requesting Customers meeting the eligibility requirements set forth herein and the execution of a Services Agreement, KGS will offer Services (which includes interstate natural Gas storage and related transportation services) to Requesting Customers on a non-discriminatory basis. A Services Agreement shall be for a term of at least one (1) Month. 3.1.2 A Requesting Customer desiring any Storage Service under this Operating Statement shall make an oral or written request to KGS by electronic mail or other electronic means (including KGS' customer activities system) which includes information such as, but not limited to: (i) the exact legal name of the Requesting Customer requesting Storage Service; (ii) the type of Storage Service(s); (iii) the proposed Maximum Daily Injection/Withdrawal Quantities that it would initially request; (iv) the Reserved Storage Capacity, Maximum Interruptible Storage Inventory, Maximum Aggregate Parking Quantity or the Maximum Aggregate Loan Quantity, depending on the Storage Service(s) requested; and, (v) the proposed term to provide the Service. 3.1.3 Any and all Transactions under this Operating Statement must be interstate Services eligible under, and shall be fully subject to, all the applicable requirements of Section 284.224 of the regulations of the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission, as they may be revised from time to time. A Customer's request for Service shall constitute its warranty that it satisfies those requirements. KGS shall have the right to request information from its Customer, whether a Requesting Customer or a Customer which has executed a Services Agreement, to verify its eligibility for Service under the applicable regulations. 3.1.4 KGS shall consider the Storage Service request and contact the Requesting Customer regarding whether it can provide such Service and, if so, will provide the details (including fees, quantity, and other essential terms) according to which KGS is willing to provide such Service. If KGS can provide some, but not all, of the requested Service, KGS will advise the Requesting Customer of the maximum quantities that KGS will be able to accommodate. A Service request shall not be valid, and KGS shall not be required to provide any such Service, if: (i) KGS determines, based on a credit analysis, that the Requesting Customer does not have credit sufficient to KGS's satisfaction as described in Section 19 below; (ii) the Service requested would require the construction, modification, expansion or acquisition of either the Facilities or any additional facilities; (iii) the Service requested would not comply with this Operating Statement; (iv) KGS lacks adequate capacity to provide the requested Service; or (v) the parties are unable to agree upon mutually acceptable fees for the Service. 3.1.5 Except as provided in paragraph 5.2 below, when the Requesting Customer and KGS have agreed upon the essential terms regarding a request for Service, KGS shall tender a Services Agreement to the Requesting Customer reflecting such agreed upon terms, and the Services Agreement shall be invalid unless executed (to include electronic execution using KGS' customer activities system) by the Requesting Customer and returned to KGS within thirty (30) days after KGS tenders the Services Agreement for execution. 3.1.6 A Customer that has executed a Services Agreement with KGS shall have the right to request specific Services pursuant to the provisions of Section 5 below.
4. FEES FOR SERVICES
The fee(s) for Services provided under the terms of this Agreement will be agreed to by KGS and Customer. The agreed upon fees will be stated in the applicable Services Agreement and/or Confirmation and in the case of a Park or Loan, may be stated as a lump sum rather than giving separate detail for each fee included.
4.1 Fees for Firm Storage or Firm Parking Services during a billing Month may include:
(a) The Demand Charge;
(b) The Commodity Charge(s);
(c) Fuel (% of Injection volume);
(d) Any applicable Overrun Rate;
(e) Any applicable Excess Inventory Rate;
(f) Any other fees agreed to by Customer and KGS that are applicable to the Firm Storage or Parking Service; and
(g) All applicable taxes, including any taxes on Fuel supplied by Customer.
4.2 Fees for Interruptible Storage or Interruptible Parking Services during a billing Month may include:
(a) The Inventory/Balance Rate;
(b) The Commodity Charge(s);
(c) Fuel (% of Injection volume);
(d) Any applicable Overrun Rate;
(e) Any applicable Excess Inventory Rate;
(f) Any other fees agreed to by Customer and KGS that are applicable to the Interruptible Storage or Parking Service; and (g) Any applicable taxes, including any taxes on Fuel supplied by Customer.
4.3 Fees for Loaning Service, whether Firm or Interruptible, during a billing Month may include:
(a) The Demand Charge (for Firm Loaning only);
(b) The Commodity Charge(s);
(c) Fuel (% of Injection volume);
(d) Any applicable Overrun Rate,
(e) Any applicable Extended Loaning Rate;
(f) Any other fees agreed to by Customer and KGS that are applicable to Loaning Service; and
(g) Any applicable taxes, including any tax on Fuel supplied by Customer.
4.4 Fees for Interruptible Wheeling Service during a billing Month may include:
(a) The Commodity Charge(s);
(b) Fuel (% of volume);
(c) Any applicable Overrun Rate;
(d) Any other fees agreed to by Customer and KGS that are applicable to the Interruptible Wheeling Service; and (e) Any applicable taxes, including any taxes on Fuel supplied by Customer.
5. PROCEDURES FOR REQUESTING SPECIFIC SERVICES
5.1 KGS and a Customer that has executed a Services Agreement may from time to time, subject to the provisions of this Section 5, enter into a Transaction where the specific terms of any such Service shall be memorialized in a Confirmation similar to the form attached to this Operating Agreement as Schedules "A", "B" "C" and "D'. Each executed Confirmation shall be for only a single type of Service: Firm or Interruptible Storage, Firm or Interruptible Parking, Firm or Interruptible Loaning or Interruptible Wheeling.
(a) For Firm Storage Service, the required terms include Reserved Storage Capacity, Transaction Period, MDIQ and MDWQ, applicable Service fees and fee structure.
(b) For Interruptible Storage Service, the required terms include the applicable Service fees and fee structure, injection, withdrawal and storage quantities and the Transaction Period.
(c) For Parking Service, the required terms include the Transaction Period, Maximum Aggregate Parking Quantity, MDIQ, MDWQ, applicable Service fees and fee structure, and whether the Service is Firm or Interruptible.
(d) For Loaning Service, the required terms include the Transaction Period, Maximum Aggregate Loaning Quantity, Maximum Daily Loan Quantity, Maximum Daily Return Quantity, applicable Service fees and fee structure, and whether the Service is Firm or Interruptible.
(e) For Interruptible Wheeling Service, the required terms include the MDTQ, applicable Service fees and fee structure, and the Transaction Period.
5.2 Once the terms of a Confirmation have been agreed upon by Customer and KGS, KGS shall submit the Confirmation to Customer for Customer's execution. KGS may submit the Confirmation to Customer by fax, electronic mail or other electronic means (including KGS' customer activities system) and Customer may execute the Confirmation and send it back to KGS by fax, electronic mail or other electronic means (including without limitation use of KGS' customer activities system). During hours occurring outside of 8 A.M. Mountain Time through 5 P.M. Mountain Time on Business Days, KGS may offer the relevant and required terms to provide a Service using electronic mail and Customer may accept those terms using electronic mail and such an agreement shall be deemed to be a Confirmation. Such an agreement shall be binding on both KGS and the Customer. For such agreements reached using electronic mail, KGS and the Customer shall execute the applicable Confirmation similar in form to Schedule A, B, C, or D with its terms within two (2) Business Days. If a Customer nominates overrun quantities for a Service after receiving an offer by KGS via electronic mail to provide such overrun service at a specified rate and term, that Nomination shall constitute acceptance of the terms offered by KGS and constitute a binding agreement on KGS and Customer and shall not require any additional writings including without limitation a Confirmation. Nothing herein shall be deemed to obligate KGS to render any Services to or enter into a Transaction with Customer until both Customer and KGS have executed a Confirmation for that Service as described by this Section 5.2.
5.3 If KGS has executed a Confirmation prior to sending it to Customer, that Confirmation shall, at the sole election of KGS and without further notice to Customer, become null and void unless executed by Customer and returned to KGS within two (2) Business Days after the date on which KGS executed the Confirmation or the date on which KGS faxed, emailed or transmitted by other electronic means (including without limitation use of KGS' customer activities system) the executed Confirmation to Customer for Customer's signature, whichever is the later date.
6. NOMINATIONS
6.1 In order to receive the Services set forth in an executed Confirmation, Customer must submit a Nomination in accordance with the procedures set forth in this Section 6.1.
a. Upon a Confirmation becoming effective, Customer shall be entitled to nominate the requested Service(s) in accordance with the terms of such Confirmation. Customer's Nomination must be made to KGS by using KGS' customer activities system at least thirty minutes prior to the applicable nomination deadline and in accordance with the NAESB's then applicable standards, as adopted by FERC. In addition the Customer's Nomination must be made to the applicable Interconnecting Pipeline on such Interconnecting Pipeline's electronic bulletin board ("EBB") in accordance with the NAESB's then applicable standards, as adopted by FERC, and the applicable Interconnecting Pipeline's nomination procedures as set out in its tariff. KGS will confirm Customer's Nomination on the applicable Interconnecting Pipeline's EBB. In the event that an Interconnecting Pipeline's tariff includes nomination cycles which exceed the then applicable NAESB standards, KGS will endeavor to accommodate such nomination cycles using commercially reasonable efforts considering the totality of the circumstances including, without limitation, the resources available at the time and additional costs required. KGS will provide notice of its ability to accommodate such cycles on its EBB. If KGS' customer activities system is unavailable, Nominations may be based on the most recent Nominations submitted by Customer via KGS' customer activities system until KGS' customer activities system is restored. However, KGS will use its best efforts to accommodate changes to such Customer directed Nominations during the period KGS' customer activities system is unavailable. KGS may waive the requirement for a Customer to submit its Nomination electronically if KGS determines, in its reasonable judgment, that Customer has experienced an event of force majeure that renders it incapable of transmitting such Nomination electronically. KGS will use its best efforts to work with Customer to enter Nomination changes Customer provides in sufficient time prior to the Nomination deadline under such limited circumstances.
b. KGS and Customer hereto (i) consent to the recording of the telephone conversations of their respective trading and marketing personnel in connection with any executed Confirmation, (ii) agree that such recording will constitute a Nomination, and (iii) agree that any such electronic recordings may be submitted in evidence in any suit, action or other proceedings in relation to this Agreement without objection to the admissibility under the statute of frauds, the hearsay rule, the best evidence rule or other rule of evidence.
c. Current contact information related to Nominations and Scheduling activity may be found on KGS' electronic bulletin board as it may change from time to time.
6.2 A Nomination made in accordance with the foregoing shall be binding on KGS and Customer, subject to the terms of this Agreement and the applicable Confirmation, and subject to acceptance by the Interconnecting Pipeline(s). Such Nomination shall remain in effect until (i) duly changed by the Customer, (ii) interrupted by KGS or the Interconnecting Pipeline for operational reasons, or, (iii) if the Transaction is for Interruptible Service, service is interrupted to serve customers with a higher Service priority, or, (iv) if the Nomination is for overrun quantities, service is interrupted to serve Firm Service or to serve Interruptible Service nominated before or at that same time as the overrun quantities, or (v) is otherwise interrupted in accordance with the terms of this Agreement or the applicable Confirmation.
6.3 Customer's Nomination shall be in good faith and shall be based on Customer's reasonable efforts to estimate the quantity of Gas to be Delivered for the next Hour, Day, Week or Month. Customer shall not intentionally nominate more or less Gas than is needed by Customer, except as may be needed for balancing purposes. Customer may not inject and withdraw simultaneously without the approval of KGS; KGS will grant or deny requests to do so on a non-discriminatory basis.
6.4 Customer or KGS may, at any time, request prospective revisions to any Nomination, once executed or otherwise made. Any such requested revisions are subject to agreement by the other Party in writing, subject to the provisions of Section 6.1.
6.5 All Nominations, scheduling, storage and priorities for Service shall be subject to demands, priorities, requests and/or constraints made or imposed by Interconnecting Pipeline(s).
6.6 KGS reserves the right to reject any Nomination(s) or decline to provide all or a portion of the Services set forth in any Confirmation(s) if the aggregate amounts payable by Customer for the requested Services, when added to all other amounts owed by Customer to KGS under this or any other Agreement, would exceed the credit limit established for Customer pursuant to Section 19 hereof.
6.7 KGS may change the foregoing Nomination procedures from time to time on thirty (30) Days prior written notice to Customer, as may be necessary to meet the operational requirements of the Interconnecting Pipeline(s) or KGS.
6.8 KGS reserves the right to pro-rate a Customer's MDIQ or MDWQ for a Nomination that takes effect after the beginning of the Day (9:00 a.m. Central Time). The Customer's partial Day MDIQ or MDWQ as applicable will be calculated by multiplying the original MDIQ or MDWQ by a fraction whose numerator is the number of Hours remaining in the Day as of the effective time of the confirmed nomination and whose denominator is twenty-four (24).
7. INTERRUPTIONS
7.1 Interruptible Services (whether Storage, Parking, Loaning, or Wheeling) hereunder are subject to interruption at any time and for any reason.
(a) To confirm and schedule Customer's Nomination for an Interruptible Service, KGS will consider the available capacity of the Facilities at that time, other Firm and Interruptible injection and withdrawal Nominations, and the aggregate quantity of Gas in storage or Nominated for Services at that time. If KGS is able to confirm Customer's Nomination, it will do so using the procedures outlined in Section 6.
(b) Customer's Interruptible Nominations for injection or withdrawal are subject to interruption at any time when Nominations for Services with a priority superior to Interruptible Service, or prior Nominations with an equal priority, exceed KGS's capacity to provide the Service(s) requested in Customer's Nomination.
(c) Customer's Nominations for Wheeling Service are subject to interruption at any time when Nominations for Services with a priority superior to Interruptible Service, or prior Nominations with an equal priority, exceed KGS's capacity to provide the Wheeling Service requested in Customer's Nomination.
(d) Subject to Section 7.3 below, Customer may be required to remove quantities of Gas previously provided to KGS under Interruptible Storage or Interruptible Parking Service, or return quantities of Gas previously loaned to the Customer under the Interruptible Lending Service. Unless otherwise agreed by Customer and KGS, any interruptible parked quantity not removed as required by Section 7 of the Operating Statement shall become the property of KGS at no cost to KGS, free and clear of any adverse claims, and, any interruptible loaned quantity not returned as required by Section 7 of the Operating Statement shall be sold to Customer as the price set forth in the notification issued by KGS described in Section 7.3 of this Operating Statement.
7.2 Firm Services under this Agreement are subject to interruptions resulting from Force Majeure, maintenance pursuant to Section 16 of this Agreement, operational flow orders and/or curtailments, whether claimed by KGS or any Interconnecting Pipeline.
7.3 KGS shall provide Customer with notice of interruptions at a time and in a manner that is prudent under then-existing conditions or as otherwise provided in this Agreement, and shall be made pursuant to the notification procedures provided in Section 23 of this Operating Statement. For notifications to a Customer to remove or return quantities of interruptible stored, parked or loaned Gas, the time period in which Customer must act will be determined based on the necessity to protect the operational integrity of KGS' system to allow KGS to fulfill higher priority commitments. However, absent a mutual agreement between KGS and such Customer, or the need to protect the operational integrity of KGS' system, in no event shall the specified time for the removal or return of interruptible stored, parked or loaned gas be less than three (3) Days from the date of KGS' initial notification. Customer shall comply with notices pursuant to this Section 7.3 in the time and manner specified in such notice. Customer shall inform its suppliers, Interconnecting Pipelines and all others whose actions are required to comply with the notice.

14. MEASUREMENT
14.1 Unit of Measurement (a) The unit of measurement for the purpose of receipt and Delivery of natural gas for any Services shall be one (1) MMBtu.
(b) The unit of volume for the purpose of measurement shall be one (1) Mcf at a base pressure of fourteen and seventy-three hundredth pounds per square inch absolute (14.73 psia) and at a base temperature of sixty degrees Fahrenheit (60?F) and the readings and registrations of metering equipment shall be computed into such units of volume as well as MMBtus.
14.2 Measuring facilities shall be installed, owned, maintained and operated, at or near the Receipt Point(s) and Delivery Point(s) for custody transfer purposes between the applicable Interconnecting Pipeline and KGS, by either KGS or the Interconnecting Pipeline(s). (a) Where custody transfer measuring facilities are installed, owned, maintained and operated by Interconnecting Pipeline(s), at or near the Receipt Point(s) and Delivery Point(s), then the applicable Interconnecting Pipeline's tariff provisions with regard to measurement shall apply.
(b) Where custody transfer measuring facilities are installed, owned, maintained and operated by KGS at or near the Receipt Point(s) and Delivery Point(s), the following shall apply to such custody transfer measuring facilities:
i. Ultrasonic meters shall be installed and operated in accordance with American Gas Association ("AGA") Report No. 9, entitled "Measurement of Gas By Multipath Ultrasonic Meters", as reprinted and revised from time to time (hereafter all referred to as "AGA Report No. 9").
ii. Orifice meters shall employ senior type primary devices with flange taps and shall be installed and operated in accordance with AGA Gas Measurement Committee Report No. 3 dated 2000 or the American Petroleum Institute ("API") Manual of Petroleum Measurement
Standards (MPMS) Chapter 14.3 (hereafter all referred to as "AGA Report No. 3") as reprinted and revised from time to time.
iii. If, upon testing, such measurement equipment is found to be in error by not more than two percent (2%), previous recordings of such equipment shall be considered accurate in computing volume of Gas Delivered, but such equipment shall be adjusted at once to record accurately. If, upon testing, the measuring equipment shall be found to be inaccurate by an amount exceeding two percent (2%), that volume shall be corrected for the period of time since the last period that the measurement equipment was known to be recording accurately or was agreed upon. In the case the period is not known or agreed upon, such correction shall be for a period extending over one-half of the time elapsed since the last test, not exceeding a correction period of sixteen (16) Days.
iv. In the event a meter operated by KGS is out of service or registering inaccurately, the volume of Gas Delivered, as applicable, shall be determined:
a) By correcting the error if the percentage of error is ascertainable by calibration, tests or mathematical calculation; or, in the absence of a), then
b) By using the registration of any check meter or meters, if installed and accurately measuring; or, in the absence of both a) and b), then
c) By estimating the volume of Gas Delivered based upon the volume of Gas Delivered during preceding periods under similar conditions (which shall include whether the Delivery of Gas was to or from the Facilities) when the meter was registering accurately.
v. Electronic Flow Measurement ("EFM") computers, transducers and other associated sensing equipment installed by KGS shall be installed and configured in accordance with API MPMS Chapter 21.1. The values for gross heating value and specific gravity shall be entered as real time data if that data is available. The values for carbon dioxide and nitrogen used in supercompressibility correction determinations shall be entered as real time data if that data is available or shall be entered manually, but at least once each Month.
14.3 Computation of Volumes (a) Where measuring facilities are installed, owned, maintained and operated by Interconnecting Pipeline(s), at or near the Receipt Point(s) and Delivery Point(s), then the applicable Interconnecting Pipeline's tariff provisions with regard to computation of volumes shall apply.
(b) For measurement of volumes within the Facilities using measurement equipment owned and operated by KGS and used for custody transfer purposes, the following measurement standards will be used for the computation of volumes:
i. All ultrasonic meter volumes shall be computed in accordance with AGA Report No. 9 as previously referenced.
ii. All orifice meter volumes shall be computed in accordance with AGA Report No. 3 as previously referenced.
iii. All turbine meter volumes shall be computed in accordance with AGA Report No. 7 as currently available and with any subsequent amendments.
iv. For positive displacement meters, metered volumes shall be measured with meters designed, constructed and installed, and whose computations of volume are made in accordance with the most current version of AGA Measurement Committee Report No. 6 and any subsequent amendments or revisions.
v. All ultrasonic, turbine, orifice and positive displacement meter volumes shall be corrected for deviations from the ideal gas laws (supercompressibility) in accordance with AGA Report No. 8 1992-1994 or API MPMS Chapter 14.2 as reprinted and revised from time to time.
vi. For the purpose of measurement, the atmospheric pressure shall be assumed to be the barometric pressure calculated for the elevation at the point of measurement.
vii. The temperature of the natural gas at the point of measurement shall be obtained by the use of a recording thermometer. The temperature of the natural gas during the measurement period shall be used in computing the Delivery of natural gas during such period.
viii. The heating value and the specific gravity shall be determined by on line chromatographic analysis of the natural gas stream at the point of measurement. The values of the physical constants for the natural gas compounds and the procedure for determining the gross heating value and/or the specific gravity of the natural gas from them shall be as set forth in the referenced AGA Report No. 8 or Gas Processors Association 2145-98 as reprinted and revised from time to time.
(c) If, at any time during the effective term of this Agreement a new method or technique is developed with respect to natural gas measurement, such new method or technique may be substituted by KGS in the exercise if its reasonable judgment. KGS shall promptly inform its Customers of any new technique adopted.
15. QUALITY
15.1 Except as otherwise provided below, all natural gas Delivered to KGS by or on behalf of Customer at the Receipt Point(s) shall conform to the following specifications:
(a) Dust, Gums and Solid Matter - The natural gas shall be commercially free from objectionable odors, solid matter, dust, gum and gum forming constituents, or any other substance which interferes with the merchantability of the Gas, or causes interference with the proper and safe operation of the pipelines, meters, regulators and other of the facilities through which it will flow. (b) Oxygen - The oxygen content shall not exceed two-tenths percent (0.2%) by volume of uncombined oxygen and every reasonable effort shall be made to keep the natural gas Delivered free of oxygen;
(c) Liquids - The natural gas shall be free of water and hydrocarbons in liquid form at the temperature and pressure at which the Gas is Delivered. The Gas shall in no event contain water vapor in excess of seven (7) pounds per million standard cubic feet;
(d) Hydrogen Sulfide - The natural gas shall not contain more than one-quarter (1/4) grain of hydrogen sulfide per one hundred (100) cubic feet;
(e) Mercaptan Sulfur - The natural gas shall not contain more than three-tenths (0.3) grain of mercaptan sulfur per one hundred (100) cubic feet;
(f) Total Sulfur - The natural gas shall not contain more than three-quarters (3/4) grain of total sulfur per one hundred (100) cubic feet;
(g) Carbon Dioxide - The natural gas shall not have a carbon dioxide content in excess of two percent (2%) by volume;
(h) Heating Value - The natural gas shall contain an average heating content of not less than nine hundred seventy (970) Btus per cubic foot nor more than one thousand fifty (1,050) Btus per cubic foot;
(i) Temperature - The natural gas shall be Delivered at temperatures not in excess of one hundred twenty degrees Fahrenheit (120?F), nor less than fifty degrees Fahrenheit (50?F);
(j) Diluents - The natural gas shall not contain in excess of three percent (3.0%) total diluents (the total combined content of carbon dioxide, nitrogen, helium, oxygen and any other diluent compound) by volume. (k) Hydrogen Dew Point - The hydrogen dew point of the natural gas received shall not exceed twenty degrees Fahrenheit (20?F) at normal pipeline operating pressures. (l) Carbonyl Sulfate - The natural gas shall not contain more than three-tenths (0.3) grains of carbonyl sulfate per one hundred standard cubic feet.
15.2 In the event natural gas being Delivered to the Facilities fails to conform to the above quality specifications, the Delivery of such natural gas may be immediately terminated, without prior notification to Customer.
15.3 KGS, at its sole option, may agree on a not unduly discriminatory basis to accept natural gas which differs from the quality specifications set forth above. The acceptance of non-conforming natural gas shall not act as a continuing or future waiver of the quality specifications in Paragraph 15.1 nor require KGS to receive natural gas of similar non-conforming quality in the future. In the event KGS does agree to accept such natural gas which differs from the quality specifications, KGS will have the continuing right to notify Customer and/or Customer's Interconnecting Pipeline that, within a specified period of time, as determined in KGS's sole discretion, all prospective volumes of natural gas to be Delivered must comply with the quality specifications set forth above or the provisions of Paragraph 15.2 shall be applicable to all natural gas Delivered to KGS which does not so comply. Customer and/or Customer's transporter shall be liable for and indemnify KGS against and reimburse KGS for all losses, damages and liabilities of any nature (including consequential damages) incurred by KGS and rising from Customer's Delivery of natural gas not in conformance with the above specifications.

With the exception of Demand Charges, which shall be billed in accordance with the applicable Confirmation, all other applicable charges and fees shall be billed based upon confirmed nominations between KGS and the Interconnecting Pipeline(s). 20.2 Payments to KGS for Services rendered during the preceding month shall be received within ten (10) days of the date of the invoice. Subject to the provision of Paragraph 20.3 below, Customer shall make such payment to KGS by wire transfer in immediately available funds to a depository designated by KGS. When the due date falls on a day that the designated depository is not open in the normal course of business to receive Customer's payment, Customer shall cause such payment to be actually received by KGS on or before the first Business Day on which the designated depository is open after such due date. 20.3 In the event that KGS is willing to accept payment by other than wire transfer, the payment to KGS for Services rendered during the preceding month shall be due on the tenth (10th) day following the date of the invoice. Customer shall cause payment for such bill to be actually received by KGS at a lock box designation by KGS, on or before such due date. 20.4 Failure to Pay Bills (a) Should Customer fail to pay KGS all of the amount of any bill when the same becomes due, Customer shall pay KGS interest on the unpaid balance that shall accrue on each calendar day from the due date at a rate equal to the lesser of (i) the prime interest rate as designated by Citibank N.A. plus five percent (5%), compounded monthly, or (ii) the maximum rate permitted by applicable law of the State of Texas. If either principal or interest is due, any payments thereafter received shall first be applied to the interest due, then to the previously outstanding principal due, and lastly, to the most current principal due.
(b) If any bill remains unpaid after the due date thereof:
i. KGS shall have the right (in addition to any other rights hereunder or at law) upon giving Customer written notice, to suspend or terminate Services and Customer, by its nonpayment of amounts due within three (3) days of receiving notice pursuant to this Section 20.4(b)(i), shall be deemed to have consented to such suspension or termination of Services; provided, that suspension will not relieve Customer of liability for any fees which accrue after the suspension.
ii. KGS hereby reserves a lien on Gas Customer may have from time to time in the Facilities pursuant to V.T.C.A. Business and Commerce Code ? 7.209. If Customer fails to pay an amount invoiced pursuant to Section 20.1 and the failure to pay continues for thirty (30) days after payment is due, KGS , in addition to any other remedy it has at law, in equity and under this Agreement shall also have the right to sell an amount of Gas held in Customer Inventory to enable KGS to recover the monies owing to it by Customer. KGS shall set off the sum of money it receives for the Gas sold, plus any and all related costs and expenses that KGS incurs in effecting the sale, against any and all monies owed to it by the Customer, including interest.
iii. If Customer in good faith disputes the amount of any bill or part thereof Customer shall pay to KGS such amount, if any, that Customer concedes to be correct. Customer and KGS shall seek to resolve disputed amounts in a timely manner. Payment of any disputed amount shall include interest calculated under Section 20.4(a) based on the original due date of such amount.
20.5 In the event that incorrect information is communicated to the Customer in any invoice that KGS renders, such error shall be adjusted within thirty (30) days of the determination thereof; provided, however, that any claim for adjustment must be made within twelve (12) Months from the date of such invoice.
20.6 Customer shall reimburse KGS within thirty (30) days of invoice thereof for all filing and other fees which are due pursuant to regulations of authorities having jurisdiction which are attributable to the execution of this Agreement.
20.7 Either Party has the right, at its sole cost, risk and expense and during the normal business hours of the Party to be audited, to audit the accounts and records of the other Party to the extent necessary to verify the statement of quantities or fees for a specific Transaction under the terms of this Agreement. Such right to audit shall not extend to accounts and records pertaining to any Transaction or other agreement for Storage Services between KGS and any third party or to any account and records pertaining to KGS's cost of providing Services or the profits thereon. Such right to audit may only be exercised within two (2) years following the date of the specific invoice(s) in dispute.
20.8 If any overcharge or undercharge has been determined and the billing therefore has been paid, the Party that has underpaid or that has been overpaid shall pay such amount to the other Party within thirty (30) days after the final determination of that under or overpayment by the Parties together with interest thereon at the rate specified in Section 20.4(a) calculated from the date such amount was originally due to the date of payment.
20.9 Customer shall pay or cause to be paid all taxes and assessments imposed on Customer with respect to Gas transported or stored prior to and including its Delivery to KGS, and KGS shall pay or cause to be paid all taxes and assessments imposed on KGS with respect to Gas transported or stored after its Delivery to KGS and prior to Delivery to Customer, provided however, that Customer shall pay to KGS all taxes, levies, fees or charges which KGS may be by law be required to collect from Customer by reason of all Services performed for Customer.
20.10 Neither Party shall be responsible or liable for any taxes or other statutory charges levied or assessed against any of the facilities of the other Party used for the purpose of carrying out the provisions of this Agreement.
20.11 Notwithstanding and in addition to but not in limitation of any other provision hereof, in the event Customer shall (i) become insolvent as evidenced in accordance with Section 19.5, (ii) fail to pay or perform, when due, any obligation under this Agreement or in connection with credit support obligations or otherwise (which, in the case of a payment default, is not remedied within thirty (30) days of the due date) or (iii) fails to provide adequate credit assurances in accordance with Section 19, then KGS shall have the right, upon written notice to Customer, to terminate all existing Transactions with Customer.
20.12 In the event KGS elects to terminate Customer's Transactions pursuant to 20.11, the following shall apply: (a) All of Customers rights for Storage Service shall immediately be terminated, as will any future payment obligations for Services under the terminated Transactions. KGS shall have no further obligation to provide Services to Customer thereafter, and shall be free to sell those Services to third parties as of the termination date in KGS's notice to Customer.
(b) Customer shall remain liable for all obligations under those terminated Transactions up to the termination date as stated in KGS's termination notice, including, but not limited to, any unbilled Demand Charges, Commodity Charges, Fuel, applicable taxes, Excess Inventory Rates or Overrun Rates for the most recent monthly period, as well as any outstanding payments due KGS hereunder.
(c) To the extent that any Customer Inventory exists at the date of termination, KGS, pursuant to Section 20.4(b)(ii) hereof, shall have the right to sell all or a portion of the Customer Inventory to offset amounts due and payable to KGS outstanding from the terminated Transactions. In such instance, KGS shall be deemed for all purposes to have acquired the Customer Inventory and to hold title thereto free and clear of all liens, encumbrances, and adverse claims whatsoever. The value of the Customer Inventory shall be the Daily Reference Price for such Gas on the Day or Days that KGS sells the Gas. Any remaining proceeds from the sale of the Customer Inventory by KGS after paying off all of Customer's outstanding obligations shall be distributed to Customer.
(d) In the event the liquidation of Customer Inventory, if any, is insufficient to satisfy all outstanding payments due KGS under the terminated Transactions, Customer shall remain liable for all outstanding obligations under the terminated Transactions, including interest thereon, and KGS shall be entitled to pursue any legal remedies available to it to secure payment.
20.13 Each Party's rights under this Section 20 are in addition to, and not in limitation or exclusion of, any other rights which a Party may have (whether by agreement, operation of law, or otherwise).

However, KGS or Customer may assign, without such consent, any of its rights hereunder to its respective parent, subsidiary or affiliate, provided that the Party so assigning shall not be released from its obligations hereunder.
24.3 Compliance with Laws. The respective obligations of the Parties to this Agreement are subject to all present and future valid laws, orders, rules and regulations of duly constituted authorities having jurisdiction over the Parties, the Facilities or Services, or this Agreement or any of its provisions. 24.4 Severance. Any provision of this Agreement that is prohibited or unenforceable shall be ineffective only to the extent of that prohibition or unenforceability without invalidating the remaining provisions of this Agreement. 24.7 Confidentiality. 24.8 Entirety. This Operating Statement and the Services Agreement, Confirmations and Nominations constitute the entire Agreement among the Parties. There are no prior or contemporaneous agreements or representations affecting such subject matter other than those expressly identified in this Agreement.
25. DEFAULT
25.1 Termination for Default. If (i) either Party shall fail in any material respect to comply with, observe, perform or shall default in any material respect upon any obligation under this Agreement, except due to causes excused by Force Majeure or attributable to the other's wrongful act or failure to act, and such failure materially and adversely affects the ability of either Party to Deliver or accept Gas and (ii) after written notice thereof from the Party claiming a right to terminate this Agreement, such failure shall continue for a period of thirty (30) days, then the Party claiming the right to terminate may, by notice in writing, terminate this Agreement as of the date of the notice of termination; provided, however, that if such failure cannot be reasonably cured within such thirty (30) days, the Party claimed to be in default shall be entitled to such further time as shall reasonably be required to effect such cure, provided that such Party commences within such thirty (30) days substantial efforts to effect such cure and at all times thereafter proceeds diligently to complete such cure.
25.2 Other Rights Preserved. The availability or exercise of the right to terminate this Agreement pursuant to this Section shall not serve to diminish or affect the right of the Parties to seek damages or specific performance, for breach of this Agreement, as provided in this Agreement.
